column5: I was wondering if it's open water or it's thin ice. Please let me know.  Thanks much!
It,s all mudded  up from the all the thaw. Right out to the lake spit/breakwall  and into the bay abit. With the wet forcast,save yer gas money.
Is the launch useable? Thinking of dragging the boat up on Saturday.
I,ll have a check and get back to you.  Im pretty sure they are open.
That would be GREAT!! It's either Simcoe or Quinte. Cant sit around the house all weekend, plus I start holidays today
The Tiffin st launch (RAMP) is clear,but there is ice chunks floating around in the water. You should be able to launch. The Marina is froze in with UNSAFE ICE.
Thanks alot. I Think I'll give it a go.
